id: pm-k2n4
title: "pm validate --check-files mis-handles remote (URL) doc/file references: flagged as deleted and silently destroyed by --prune-missing"
description: "A linked artifact `path` (pm files / pm docs) is normally a workspace-relative or absolute local filesystem path, but `pm docs --add` legitimately records REMOTE references too — most commonly an `https://` URL to a pull request, issue, or external design doc (e.g. pm-bhmk/pm-v37g/pm-qawd each link https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/362|364). These remote references are not local files, yet three validation surfaces blindly `fs.stat` them:\n\n1. buildFilesCheck (src/cli/commands/validate.ts ~L1666): every project-scoped files+docs artifact is stat'd; a URL resolves to a bogus local path -> stat fails -> pushed to missing_linked_paths and staleLinkRows.\n2. classifyStaleLinkedPaths then labels it `deleted` (no basename candidate match).\n3. planStaleLinkPruneFixes (src/core/validate/fix-planning.ts) prunes every `deleted`-classified link -> `pm validate --prune-missing` SILENTLY DELETES the intentionally-recorded PR/URL doc reference. This is data loss of recorded context (project management = context management).\n4. validateLinkedPaths (src/cli/commands/linked-artifacts.ts ~L402) used by `pm files/docs --validate-paths` reports the URL as a missing_path for the same reason.\n\nImpact: false-positive validator noise (URL refs counted among the 148 missing_linked_paths seen on this repo, inflating pm-j8z6's reconciliation backlog) AND a latent destructive-fix bug. Follow-up to pm-0v2m (GH-184) which introduced moved/deleted classification + --prune-missing without remote-reference awareness."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:cli",context-management,data-safety,linked-files
created_at: "2026-06-26T04:13:20.706Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-26T04:37:46.946Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Added pure helper isRemoteLinkedArtifactReference (scheme:// detection, 2+ char scheme so Windows drive/UNC paths stay local) and wired it into buildFilesCheck (validate.ts) and validateLinkedPaths (linked-artifacts.ts): remote (URL) refs are now surfaced in benign remote_linked_paths / remote_references categories and are never stat'd, classified moved/deleted, counted missing, or planned for --prune-missing. Shipped in PR #372."
expected_result: "A recorded https:// doc reference (e.g. a PR URL) stays a benign tracked reference; pm validate --check-files does not report it as missing/deleted and pm validate --prune-missing never deletes it."
actual_result: "Before the fix the URL fs.stat-failed, was classified 'deleted', and was planned for deletion by --prune-missing (silent data loss); after the fix it appears under remote_linked_paths and is never pruned (verified by temp-dir smoke + unit tests)."
