close_reason: "Fixed in PR #372: remote (URL) doc/file references are now recognized and excluded from local-file existence checks, missing/stale classification, and --prune-missing. Verified by 5131-test 100% coverage suite, contracts/static/changelog gates, and a temp-dir end-to-end smoke. CI green across the full matrix; CodeRabbit review clean (1 nitpick addressed); Gemini at daily quota / Codex not connected this cycle."
body: "## Implementation (branch fix/validate-remote-reference-awareness)\n\nNew pure module `src/core/validate/linked-artifact-reference.ts` exposing `isRemoteLinkedArtifactReference(path)` — matches `^[a-z][a-z0-9+.-]+:\\/\\//i` (scheme of 2+ chars + `://` authority) so `https://`/`ftp://`/`ssh://`/`file://` are remote while `C:/…`, `C:\\…`, `//server/share`, relative and absolute POSIX paths are local.\n\nWired into both stat-based surfaces:\n- `buildFilesCheck` (src/cli/commands/validate.ts): remote refs are collected into a new benign `remote_linked_paths{,_count,_total,_truncated}` details category and `continue` before the existence probe — so they never enter `missing_linked_paths`, `staleLinkRows`, classification, or `staleLinkPruneRows`.\n- `validateLinkedPaths` (src/cli/commands/linked-artifacts.ts): remote refs go to a new `remote_references[]` field instead of `missing_paths` (surfaced by `pm files/docs --validate-paths`).\n\n## Verification\n\nManual temp-dir smoke (real built CLI, `pm init` + Task with a real file, a missing local file, and a PR URL doc ref):\n- `validate --check-files`: `remote_linked_paths_count=1` (the PR URL), `missing_linked_paths=['ghost-file.ts']` only — URL not flagged.\n- `validate --prune-missing --dry-run`: single planned fix `pm files <id> --remove \"ghost-file.ts\"` — the URL doc ref is NEVER targeted (data-loss bug fixed).\n- `pm docs --validate-paths`: `remote_references=['https://…/pull/362']`, `missing_paths=[]`.\n\nGates: `pnpm typecheck` clean; targeted suites 122/122 pass; `contracts:check` current; `quality:static` (incl. docstring coverage) passes. Full 100% coverage gate running."
